Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and finely dice @bell pepper{1}(finely diced). Halve, peel, and finely dice @onion{1}(finely diced). Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Quarter @lime{1}. Finely chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}(finely chopped).

Heat a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @peanuts{½%ounce}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and @water{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in pan used for peanuts over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until tender and lightly browned, ~{5-8%minutes}. Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Open and drain @tofu{1}; press out excess water with #paper towels{} and cut into ¾-inch cubes. Add tofu; season with salt and pepper. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up tofu into pieces and cook until cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

> Alternatively, swap in chicken for tofu. No need to break up chicken into pieces!

Return veggies to pan. Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until mixture is thoroughly coated, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Divide lettuce leaves between plates; fill with tofu mixture. Garnish with candied peanuts and cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> TIP: Alternatively, serve tofu mixture, candied peanuts, and cilantro in separate bowls and let everyone assemble their own wraps!